title: H.S. FOOTBALL ROUNDUP: Donohue sparks Cohasset
text: H.S. FOOTBALL ROUNDUP: Donohue sparks Cohasset Jack Donohue scored three TDs in the third quarter Friday night as the Skippers blanked Pope John Paul II, 24-0, at home. Comment The Patriot Ledger, Quincy, MA By Staff reports   10:40 PM Updated at 10:48 PM   10:40 PM Updated at 10:48 PM Senior captain Jack Donohue did a little bit of everything Friday night in leading the Cohasset High football team to a 24-0 home win over Pope John Paul II. Donohue, a tight end/defensive end, accounted for all three Skippers touchdowns – two on catches (of 5 and 40 yards) and one on a 55-yard fumble return. He also defended three passes and made two tackles for losses for Cohasset (4-1). “He had a monster game,” coach Pete Afanasiw said. Senior kicker Henry Butenschoen kicked a 27-yard field goal for the only points of the first half and then was 3 for 3 on PATs as the Skippers broke the game open on Donohue’s trio of third-quarter TDs. Cole Sullivan added seven tackles, a sack and a blocked punt. He also forced the fumble that Donohue returned for a score. “It was a little bit of conditioning,” Afanasiw said of Cohasset’s second-half explosion. “We wore them down. (Pope John Paul) had a lot of guys playing both ways. “We also made some subtle halftime adjustments that paid off.” In other high school football action: Scituate 42, Pembroke 8: The Sailors (3-2, 2-1) rolled to a Patriot League Fisher Division road win over the Titans (0-5, 0-3) as Colin May (7 carries for 101 yards) had TD runs of 6 and 57 yards. Peter Churchill ran 39 yards for a score and threw a 6-yard TD pass to Devin Gantt. Scituate’s other touchdowns came from Noah Pillsbury (32-yard interception return) and Peyton Crosby (23-yard run). Jake Bridgeman was 6 for 6 on PATs. Pembroke’s touchdown came on a 13-yard reception by Joe Benting. Milton 26, Norwood 14: The Wildcats (5-0, 3-0 Bay State Conference Herget Division) raced out to a 26-0 lead in the first half and hung on to win at Norwood (3-2, 1-2). Carver 42, Monomoy 0: The Crusaders (3-2, 1-1) won a South Shore League Small game that was halted in the third quarter due to lightning. St. Mary’s (Lynn) 32, Archbishop Williams 8: Marcus McBean rushed 23 times for 144 yards and a TD, but the Bishops (3-2, 0-2) lost to Catholic Central League Large rival St. Mary’s (4-1, 2-0) at home. Marshfield 50, Falmouth 7: The host Rams (5-0, 2-0) took sole possession of first place in the Atlantic Coast League, breaking a tie with Falmouth (4-1, 1-1). BC High 17, Malden Catholic 14: The Eagles (4-1) won their Catholic Conference opener at MC (3-2, 0-2) as Marco King threw a pair of TD passes and Jarod Mockus kicked a 24-yard field goal. Needham 21, Weymouth 10: The Wildcats (3-2, 2-1) lost a Bay State Conference Carey Division showdown at Needham (3-2, 3-0). Page 2 of 2 - Mashpee 42, Hull 20: The Pirates (1-4, 1-2) lost a South Shore League Small game at home to Mashpee (3-2, 2-1). Abington 21, Seekonk 6: The Green Wave (4-1) won a non-league game at Seekonk (1-3). Shawn Donovan returned a punt 70 yards for a touch down to open the scoring, and Brendan Glavin (28-yard run) and Donnel Leon (34-yard run) added scores. Hanover 20, Plymouth South 6: The Indians (4-1, 3-0) picked up a Patriot League Fisher Division road win over the Panthers (2-3, 0-3). By Staff reports The Patriot Ledger, Quincy, MA By Staff reports   10:40 PM Updated at 10:48 PM
